    {
      "id": 3, "type": "text", "title": "Temporal model & Date Range",
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 5 },
      "options": { "mode": "markdown", "content": "**Temporal basis.** The only governed field with real temporal spread is **`forecast_version`** (14 versions, 2024-04 → 2026-05); every timeline record is a governed drift event (`is_event = 1`) placed at its forecast_version (*Date Basis = Forecast Version*). **`detected_on` = `created_at` = `changed_at`** all equal a single detection instant (**2026-07-13 22:38 UTC**), so *Drift Detected* is a governed fact, not a spread timeline. The lifecycle table holds **71 initial `Open` records with 0 true status transitions** — no status-change sequence is fabricated. No *Forecast Generated* or *Alert Triggered* activity exists in the governed snapshot, so none is shown.\n\n**Date Range.** The **Date Range** variable filters by `forecast_version` (windows: All / Year to date / Last 180·90·60·30 days / Year 2024·2025·2026). The native time picker is hidden because the Infinity CSV backend does not honor the dashboard time range. Latest Governed Run and Data Quality are global (run-scoped)." }
    },

